    "To ensure training exercise intensity was reflective of medication effects, all participants were instructed to take their usual medications before the maximal exercise test.",
    "Hospital Recruitment Screening eligibility criteria: medical history, physical examination, ECG, biochemical analysis The informed consent obtained Assessed for eligibility (n=308) End of Intervention MEASUREMENTS -Blood analysis -Lifestyle and health behavior -Body composition -Aerobic capacity -Muscle strength -Physical activity/sedentatism behavior -Quality of life questionaires -Hospital Anxiety and Drepression Scale Exercise Testing (Bruce Test) Baseline measurements Randomization (N=72) Intervention (6 weeks) HIIT group (n=24) MICT group (n=24) Control group (n=24) Dropped out (n=1) -Lost interest (n=1) Dropped out (n=1) -Reduce adherence (n=1) Dropped out (n=1) -Lost interest (n=1) Excluded (n=236) -Not meeting inclusion criteria (n=225) -Declined to praticipate (n=5) -Electrically-positive baseline exercise test (n=6) Inclusion criteria: CAD event; age >18-80 years; NYHA functional class I, II; LVEF ≥ 45% 6-month follow-up measurements 12-month follow-up measurements Usual medical recommendations (mediterranean diet and physical activity) Usual medical recommendations (mediterranean diet and physical activity) + supervised exercise Usual medical recommendations (mediterranean diet and physical activity) + supervised exercise Post-Intervention measurements Analized (n=23) Analized (n=23) Analized (n=23)",
    "Blood samples were drawn on the same day as exercise testing but were collected before exercise.",
    "All final blood samples were obtained 24-48 h after completion of the last exercise session.",
